<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>ISO 9001 Quality Management System Manual - Sample Documentation</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #f5f5f5;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            background: white;
            padding: 30px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
            position: relative;
        }
        .watermark {
            position: fixed;
            top: 50%;
            left: 50%;
            transform: translate(-50%, -50%) rotate(-45deg);
            font-size: 120px;
            color: rgba(0, 123, 255, 0.08);
            font-weight: bold;
            z-index: 1;
            pointer-events: none;
            user-select: none;
        }
        .header {
            text-align: center;
            border-bottom: 3px solid #007bff;
            padding-bottom: 20px;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
            position: relative;
            z-index: 2;
        }
        .logo {
            font-size: 24px;
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #007bff;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }
        h1 {
            color: #333;
            margin: 20px 0;
            font-size: 28px;
        }
        h2 {
            color: #007bff;
            border-left: 4px solid #007bff;
            padding-left: 15px;
            margin-top: 30px;
        }
        h3 {
            color: #555;
            margin-top: 25px;
        }
        .document-info {
            background: #f8f9fa;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin-bottom: 25px;
            position: relative;
            z-index: 2;
        }
        .info-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
            gap: 15px;
        }
        .info-item {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
            padding: 8px 0;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #dee2e6;
        }
        .info-label {
            font-weight: 600;
            color: #495057;
        }
        .info-value {
            color: #6c757d;
        }
        .section {
            margin-bottom: 30px;
            position: relative;
            z-index: 2;
        }
        .iso-principle {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #007bff, #0056b3);
            color: white;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }
        .iso-principle h3 {
            color: white;
            margin-top: 0;
        }
        .principles-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
            gap: 20px;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }
        .principle-card {
            background: #f8f9fa;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            border-left: 4px solid #007bff;
            height: fit-content;
        }
        .principle-number {
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #007bff;
            font-size: 16px;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }
        .principle-title {
            font-weight: 600;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            color: #333;
        }
        .principle-desc {
            font-size: 14px;
            color: #6c757d;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }
        .process-approach {
            display: inline-block;
            padding: 4px 12px;
            border-radius: 20px;
            font-size: 12px;
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-top: 10px;
        }
        .plan { background: #fff3cd; color: #856404; }
        .do { background: #d1ecf1; color: #0c5460; }
        .check { background: #f8d7da; color: #721c24; }
        .act { background: #d4edda; color: #155724; }
        .qms-table {
            width: 100%;
            border-collapse: collapse;
            margin: 20px 0;
            background: white;
        }
        .qms-table th, .qms-table td {
            border: 1px solid #dee2e6;
            padding: 12px;
            text-align: left;
            vertical-align: top;
        }
        .qms-table th {
            background-color: #007bff;
            color: white;
            font-weight: 600;
        }
        .qms-table tr:nth-child(even) {
            background-color: #f8f9fa;
        }
        .quality-objective {
            background: #e8f5e8;
            border: 1px solid #c3e6c3;
            padding: 15px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin: 15px 0;
        }
        .objective-title {
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #155724;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }
        .context-matrix {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr 1fr 1fr;
            gap: 1px;
            background: #dee2e6;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }
        .matrix-header {
            background: #007bff;
            color: white;
            padding: 15px;
            font-weight: bold;
            text-align: center;
        }
        .matrix-cell {
            background: white;
            padding: 12px;
            text-align: center;
        }
        .pdca-cycle {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
            grid-template-rows: 1fr 1fr;
            gap: 10px;
            margin: 20px 0;
            height: 300px;
        }
        .pdca-plan {
            background: #fff3cd;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
        }
        .pdca-do {
            background: #d1ecf1;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
        }
        .pdca-check {
            background: #f8d7da;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
        }
        .pdca-act {
            background: #d4edda;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
        }
        .pdca-title {
            font-weight: bold;
            font-size: 18px;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }
        .footer {
            margin-top: 40px;
            padding-top: 20px;
            border-top: 2px solid #007bff;
            text-align: center;
            color: #6c757d;
            font-size: 14px;
            position: relative;
            z-index: 2;
        }
        .sample-badge {
            position: absolute;
            top: 10px;
            right: 10px;
            background: #dc3545;
            color: white;
            padding: 5px 15px;
            border-radius: 20px;
            font-size: 12px;
            font-weight: bold;
            z-index: 3;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="watermark">SAMPLE</div>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="sample-badge">SAMPLE DOCUMENT</div>
        
        <div class="header">
            <div class="logo">PRISM WRITING</div>
            <h1>Quality Management System Manual<br>
            ISO 9001:2015 Implementation</h1>
            <p><strong>Professional Quality Management Documentation</strong></p>
        </div>

        <div class="document-info">
            <div class="info-grid">
                <div class="info-item">
                    <span class="info-label">Document ID:</span>
                    <span class="info-value">QMS-MANUAL-2024</span>
                </div>
                <div class="info-item">
                    <span class="info-label">ISO Standard:</span>
                    <span class="info-value">ISO 9001:2015</span>
                </div>
                <div class="info-item">
                    <span class="info-label">Version:</span>
                    <span class="info-value">3.2</span>
                </div>
                <div class="info-item">
                    <span class="info-label">Effective Date:</span>
                    <span class="info-value">January 1, 2024</span>
                </div>
                <div class="info-item">
                    <span class="info-label">Next Review:</span>
                    <span class="info-value">December 2024</span>
                </div>
                <div class="info-item">
                    <span class="info-label">Quality Manager:</span>
                    <span class="info-value">Sarah Johnson, CQM</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>1. Organization Context and QMS Scope</h2>
            <p>Our Quality Management System (QMS) is designed to consistently provide products and services that meet customer and applicable statutory and regulatory requirements, and to enhance customer satisfaction through effective application of the system and continual improvement processes.</p>
            
            <h3>1.1 Organizational Context</h3>
            <p>We have determined the internal and external issues that are relevant to our purpose and strategic direction and that affect our ability to achieve the intended results of our QMS:</p>
            
            <div class="context-matrix">
                <div class="matrix-header">Issue Type</div>
                <div class="matrix-header">Description</div>
                <div class="matrix-header">Impact</div>
                <div class="matrix-header">Management</div>
                
                <div class="matrix-cell"><strong>External - Market</strong></div>
                <div class="matrix-cell">Increasing competition and customer expectations</div>
                <div class="matrix-cell">High</div>
                <div class="matrix-cell">Strategic planning</div>
                
                <div class="matrix-cell"><strong>External - Regulatory</strong></div>
                <div class="matrix-cell">Evolving compliance requirements</div>
                <div class="matrix-cell">Medium</div>
                <div class="matrix-cell">Compliance monitoring</div>
                
                <div class="matrix-cell"><strong>Internal - Technology</strong></div>
                <div class="matrix-cell">Digital transformation initiatives</div>
                <div class="matrix-cell">High</div>
                <div class="matrix-cell">IT modernization</div>
                
                <div class="matrix-cell"><strong>Internal - Human Resources</strong></div>
                <div class="matrix-cell">Skills development and retention</div>
                <div class="matrix-cell">Medium</div>
                <div class="matrix-cell">Training programs</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>2. Quality Management Principles</h2>
            
            <div class="principles-grid">
                <div class="principle-card">
                    <div class="principle-number">Principle 1</div>
                    <div class="principle-title">Customer Focus</div>
                    <div class="principle-desc">Primary focus on meeting customer requirements and striving to exceed customer expectations.</div>
                    <span class="process-approach plan">Customer-Centric</span>
                </div>
                
                <div class="principle-card">
                    <div class="principle-number">Principle 2</div>
                    <div class="principle-title">Leadership</div>
                    <div class="principle-desc">Leaders establish unity of purpose and create conditions for people to be engaged in achieving quality objectives.</div>
                    <span class="process-approach do">Direction Setting</span>
                </div>
                
                <div class="principle-card">
                    <div class="principle-number">Principle 3</div>
                    <div class="principle-title">Engagement of People</div>
                    <div class="principle-desc">Competent, empowered and engaged people at all levels enhance organization's capability to create value.</div>
                    <span class="process-approach check">Empowerment</span>
                </div>
                
                <div class="principle-card">
                    <div class="principle-number">Principle 4</div>
                    <div class="principle-title">Process Approach</div>
                    <div class="principle-desc">Understanding and managing interrelated processes as a system contributes to effectiveness and efficiency.</div>
                    <span class="process-approach act">System Thinking</span>
                </div>
                
                <div class="principle-card">
                    <div class="principle-number">Principle 5</div>
                    <div class="principle-title">Improvement</div>
                    <div class="principle-desc">Successful organizations have an ongoing focus on improvement and innovation.</div>
                    <span class="process-approach plan">Continuous</span>
                </div>
                
                <div class="principle-card">
                    <div class="principle-number">Principle 6</div>
                    <div class="principle-title">Evidence-based Decision Making</div>
                    <div class="principle-desc">Decisions based on analysis and evaluation of data and information are more likely to produce desired results.</div>
                    <span class="process-approach do">Data-Driven</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>3. Plan-Do-Check-Act (PDCA) Cycle</h2>
            
            <div class="iso-principle">
                <h3>PDCA Methodology</h3>
                <p>Our QMS applies the PDCA methodology to all processes to ensure systematic approach to improvement and risk-based thinking throughout the organization.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="pdca-cycle">
                <div class="pdca-plan">
                    <div class="pdca-title">PLAN</div>
                    <div>Establish objectives and processes necessary to deliver results in accordance with customer requirements and organization policies</div>
                </div>
                <div class="pdca-do">
                    <div class="pdca-title">DO</div>
                    <div>Implement the processes as planned and controlled manner</div>
                </div>
                <div class="pdca-check">
                    <div class="pdca-title">CHECK</div>
                    <div>Monitor and measure processes and products against policies, objectives and requirements</div>
                </div>
                <div class="pdca-act">
                    <div class="pdca-title">ACT</div>
                    <div>Take actions to improve performance, as necessary, based on evaluation results</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>4. QMS Process Architecture</h2>
            <h3>4.1 Core Business Processes</h3>
            <table class="qms-table">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Process Category</th>
                        <th>Process Name</th>
                        <th>Process Owner</th>
                        <th>Key Performance Indicators</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td rowspan="3"><strong>Management Processes</strong></td>
                        <td>Strategic Planning</td>
                        <td>Executive Leadership</td>
                        <td>Goal achievement rate, ROI</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Management Review</td>
                        <td>Quality Manager</td>
                        <td>Review completion, Action closure</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Risk Management</td>
                        <td>Risk Manager</td>
                        <td>Risk mitigation effectiveness</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td rowspan="4"><strong>Core Processes</strong></td>
                        <td>Customer Requirements</td>
                        <td>Sales Manager</td>
                        <td>Requirements clarity, Change rate</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Design & Development</td>
                        <td>Engineering Manager</td>
                        <td>Design reviews, Time to market</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Production/Service Delivery</td>
                        <td>Operations Manager</td>
                        <td>On-time delivery, Quality rate</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Customer Service</td>
                        <td>Customer Service Manager</td>
                        <td>Customer satisfaction, Response time</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td rowspan="3"><strong>Support Processes</strong></td>
                        <td>Human Resources</td>
                        <td>HR Manager</td>
                        <td>Training effectiveness, Retention</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Purchasing</td>
                        <td>Procurement Manager</td>
                        <td>Supplier performance, Cost savings</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Information Technology</td>
                        <td>IT Manager</td>
                        <td>System availability, Security incidents</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>5. Quality Objectives and Planning</h2>
            <h3>5.1 Quality Objectives 2024</h3>
            
            <div class="quality-objective">
                <div class="objective-title">Customer Satisfaction Objective</div>
                <p><strong>Target:</strong> Achieve 95% customer satisfaction rating<br>
                <strong>Measurement:</strong> Quarterly customer satisfaction surveys<br>
                <strong>Resources:</strong> Customer service training, feedback systems<br>
                <strong>Responsibility:</strong> Customer Service Manager<br>
                <strong>Timeline:</strong> Quarterly reviews, annual target</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="quality-objective">
                <div class="objective-title">Process Efficiency Objective</div>
                <p><strong>Target:</strong> Reduce process cycle time by 15%<br>
                <strong>Measurement:</strong> Process performance metrics<br>
                <strong>Resources:</strong> Process improvement team, automation tools<br>
                <strong>Responsibility:</strong> Operations Manager<br>
                <strong>Timeline:</strong> Monthly monitoring, quarterly optimization</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="quality-objective">
                <div class="objective-title">Quality Performance Objective</div>
                <p><strong>Target:</strong> Maintain defect rate below 0.5%<br>
                <strong>Measurement:</strong> Quality control data analysis<br>
                <strong>Resources:</strong> Quality control systems, training programs<br>
                <strong>Responsibility:</strong> Quality Assurance Manager<br>
                <strong>Timeline:</strong> Daily monitoring, weekly reporting</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>6. Risk-Based Thinking Implementation</h2>
            <h3>6.1 Risk Assessment Matrix</h3>
            <p>We have implemented risk-based thinking throughout our QMS to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Determine factors that could cause processes and QMS to deviate from planned results</li>
                <li>Put in place preventive controls to minimize negative effects</li>
                <li>Make maximum use of opportunities as they arise</li>
            </ul>
            
            <table class="qms-table">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Risk Category</th>
                        <th>Risk Description</th>
                        <th>Probability</th>
                        <th>Impact</th>
                        <th>Mitigation Strategy</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Operational</td>
                        <td>Supply chain disruption</td>
                        <td>Medium</td>
                        <td>High</td>
                        <td>Multiple supplier qualification</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Regulatory</td>
                        <td>Changing compliance requirements</td>
                        <td>High</td>
                        <td>Medium</td>
                        <td>Regular regulatory monitoring</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Technology</td>
                        <td>System failure or cyber attack</td>
                        <td>Low</td>
                        <td>High</td>
                        <td>Backup systems, cybersecurity measures</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Human Resources</td>
                        <td>Key personnel departure</td>
                        <td>Medium</td>
                        <td>Medium</td>
                        <td>Knowledge management, succession planning</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>

        <div class="footer">
            <p><strong>Sample Document Created by Prism Writing</strong></p>
            <p>This is a professional documentation sample demonstrating ISO 9001:2015 Quality Management System implementation.<br>
            Contact us for custom quality management documentation and process improvement services.</p>
            <p><em>© 2024 Prism Writing Cooperative - Professional Technical Documentation</em></p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
